      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOUBLE HELIX (3) was fast away from wide out with an impressive early sectional and went on to clock 30.24 in a 7 length win at this track over 530m. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. Looks to have an edge on most of these. DURAN PANTERA (5) had been in super honest form hitting the frame three times on end before finishing fourth (34.79) at this track last time. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of four starts. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. WEBLEC STELLA (7) was the fastest winner on the program last time out, running away to score by 2.5 lengths (34.31) at this track. Looks suited and is one of the contenders. ZIPPING NORRIS (1) placed last time (25.89) at Murray Bridge in a Grade 6, finishing third and beaten half a length. Has three wins already from this draw.",
